  title: 'Getting started with the Android Large Screen changes'
  sections:
  - heading: Overview
    text: 'The first step to suppore Large Screen optimized support in your Unity project is to update the AndroidManifest file to support
	the OnConfigurationChanged event.  The Unity activity does not expose this event to the C# portion of the engine,
	and you will need to modify the project by selecting the Export Project option from the Build Settings window.'
    linkText: More info
    url: https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/resources/runtime-changes
  - heading: "Step 0: Export AndroidManifest"
    text: Project Settings -> Player -> Publishing Settings -> Custom Main Manifest
    linkText: Android App Manifest
    url: https://docs.unity3d.com/Manual/android-manifest.html
  - heading: "Step 1: Handle Safe Area properly"
    text: Update root canvas to respond to Safe Area.  This involves adding a component to a root Panel under your main canvas. The GameObject "Panel-SafeArea" demonstrates this in the hierarchy.  The left/right and jump controls are then moved and anchored properly to the bottom left and right of the safe area, respectively.
    linkText: About Safe Area
    url: https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Screen-safeArea.html
  - heading: "Step 2: Modify OnConfigurationChanged event"
    text: Info here
    linkText: onConfigurationChanged function
    url: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/app/Activity#onConfigurationChanged(android.content.res.Configuration)
